title: Tax cut with some crowding out increases GDP

content.question: If crowding out only partially offsets the effects of a tax cut, which of the following changes in interest rates and gross domestic product are most likely to occur?

choices.label: Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Increase Increase
Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Increase Remain unchanged
Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Increase Decrease
Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Remain unchanged Increase
Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Decrease Decrease

content.answer: Interest Rates Gross Domestic Product Increase Increase

skill.text: Skill 3.B: Determine the effect(s) of one or more changes on other economic markets.
